## Legacy elimination policy

**Legacy code, data, terminology, compatibility paths, and obsolete stack references are debt.**

- Do not preserve, extend, or add backward compatibility for legacy formats, APIs, UI flows, build paths, or project data.
- Remove legacy code in the same change when it is encountered. A compatibility branch, fallback parser, adapter, alias, or conversion shim is a **BLOCKER** unless the user explicitly authorizes a short-lived exception with a tracked removal issue.
- Saved-project format changes must use an explicit version bump and current-format fixtures/round-trip tests. Older formats must fail clearly; they are not converted or silently normalized.
- ArtCade is Qt/QML + C++ only. Obsolete UI stacks and references to them are debt and must be removed rather than documented, adapted, or revived.
- Review every modified symbol for legacy references. Remove them before commit; do not leave a TODO, compatibility comment, or dead adapter behind.

